Additionally, PLA sticks well to blue painter's tape, extra hair spray, and "ABS Juice" (scrap ABS filament dissolved in acetone).

The image provides tips for printing with PLA material on a heated print bed, suggesting a temperature range of 195°C - 215°C. It highlights that PLA can be printed with or without a heated bed, but a heated bed is recommended at approximately 60°C - 80°C. The first layer should be 5°C - 10°C higher than subsequent layers, and it glows in the dark at this temperature. Additionally, PLA sticks well to blue painter's tape, extra hair spray, and "ABS Juice" (scrap ABS filament dissolved in acetone).
